				<p>For vegetarians &#8212; you can make any kind of soup or gravy that would normally have a brown-stock base with vegetable stock!  And it will taste right!  Just add a good spoonful (or more &#8212; it depends on how much stock you are using, so you need to taste this to check the amounts) of Marmite when you add the stock (and yes, Marmite is fairly vile by itself, but it does amazing things to vegetarian soups &amp; gravies).  It works, I swear.</p>
