				<p>Made this AGAIN for dinner, with the Sally Lunn batter bread (made with less sugar, so not as sweet)&#8230;and it&#8217;s yummy wonderfulness. Don&#8217;t know why some commenters seem to think this isn&#8217;t economical. Gruyere is expensive, but I just grate and freeze it in ziplocks and a chunk will last me FOREVER&#8230;and still is much cheaper than a meat-based dish. People who don&#8217;t do wine need not shy away from the dish; just use a bit more stock or water. It&#8217;ll just lose a tad in flavor. </p>
