<li class="commentbody highlighted" id="comment-1404467">
			<cite><a href='http://smittenkitchen.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>deb</a></cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-1404467" title="">January 3, 2012</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">365</div>

				<p>Vicki &#8212; One of the not-so-pleasant secrets of French Onion Soup is that most contain quite a bit of salt. At restaurants, especially so, so if you&#8217;re trying to match it, you&#8217;ll need more than I suggest. It&#8217;s because caramelized onions have a lot of sugars in them (well, all onions do, caramelization pronounces it) so salt helps. Sherry is a bit sweeter, but I wouldn&#8217;t guess that it&#8217;s so much that it would throw the whole recipe. Hope that helps, or at least adds insight!</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
<li class="commentbody" id="comment-1413797">
			<cite><a href='http://birdsandseahells.blogspot.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Vicki</a></cite>
